headline: Southwest Seen Government Adjacent Business Fall On Shutdown
summary: Southwest Airlines tumbled after the carrier said the US government shutdown is starting to ripple across domestic flying, threatening the record sales it expects during the crucial holiday period. headline: Government shutdown impact on Southwest is 'relatively modest': CFO
summary: The airline industry is in focus amid the ongoing US government shutdown with flight safety risks and long-term sector impacts among the chief concerns raised by experts. Southwest Airlines' (LUV) fourth quarter outlook projects record high operating revenue even with the "modest" impact of the shutdown. Southwest CFO Tom Doxey joins Morning Brief to discuss the impacts on the company as the shutdown stretches into its fourth week. headline: Tesla slumps, American Airlines earnings, Russian oil: 3 Things
summary: US stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) are in the red as markets continue to digest earnings results from top companies. Tesla (TSLA) shares are under pressure Thursday morning after topping third quarter revenue estimates but coming up just shy of Wall Street's expectations on quarterly earnings. American Airlines (AAL) stock is soaring, and Southwest Airlines (LUV) shares are getting a boost after the two airline operators posted strong third quarter earnings results.. Oil prices (CL=F, BZ=F) have jumped as the Trump administration increases pressure on Russia by unveiling new sanctions on Russian oil producers. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.
